assignOrganization(address,bytes32).details: This function can be called by:  - A global admin (DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE) for any organization.  - A tenant admin (TENANT_ADMIN_ROLE) but only for the tenant admin's own organization.

params.account: The user to be assigned to the organization.
params.organizationId: The ID of the organization to assign.

configureTenantAdmin(address,bytes32).details: Can only be called by an account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE.

params.organizationId: The organization that the tenant admin will manage.
params.tenantAdmin: The address to grant the TENANT_ADMIN_ROLE.

params.credentialManagerAddr: The address of the credential manager contract.
params.didManagerAddr: The address of the DID manager contract.
params.discrepancyManagerAddr: The address of the discrepancy manager contract.
params.governmentDID: The DID of the government entity.
params.signatureManagerAddr: The address of the signature manager contract.

params.didHash: The DID hash for manufacturer validation.
params.externalURN: The external, standards-compliant URN or pointer to a DID document.
params.nonce: The current nonce for the caller

eip712Domain().details: returns the fields and values that describe the domain separator used by this contract for EIP-712 signature.

params.tokenId: The token ID to look up.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.structHash: The struct hash to calculate the digest for.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.updater: The address authorized to perform updates for the organization.

returns._0: True if the interface is supported, false otherwise.

params.from: The current owner of the passport.
params.nonce: The current nonce for the caller.
params.to: The new owner of the passport.
params.tokenId: The token ID of the passport to transfer.

params.current: The current status of the battery.
params.next: The next status to transition to.

returns._0: True if the transition is valid, false otherwise.

params.didHash: The DID hash for government validation.
params.nonce: The current nonce for the caller.
params.tokenId: The token ID of the passport to verify.

returns._0: True if the IPFS hash is valid, false otherwise.

assignOrganization(address,bytes32).notice: Assigns an organization to a user.

configureTenantAdmin(address,bytes32).notice: Configures a tenant admin for a specific organization.

constructor.notice: Initializes the contract with the provided manager addresses and government DID.

createBatteryPassport(bytes32,string,str.notice: Creates a new battery passport with dual-hash storage and nonce-based replay protection.

getBatteryPassport(uint256).notice: Returns the entire BatteryPassport struct for the given tokenId.

getPassport(uint256).notice: Returns the full BatteryPassport struct for a given token ID.

getUserOrganization(address).notice: Returns the organization ID associated with a user.

hashTypedDataV4(bytes32).notice: Calculates the EIP-712 digest for a given struct hash.

incrementNonce(address).notice: Increments the nonce for a signer. Callable by the updater contract.

initializeRoles().notice: Initializes admin mappings so tenant admins can grant operational roles.

isAuthorizedLifecycleUpdater(bytes32,add.notice: Checks if a signer is authorized to update lifecycle status. Tenant updaters, recyclers, and global admins are authorized.

setBatteryPassportUpdater(address).notice: Sets the updater contract address. Can only be set once.

setTenantUpdater(bytes32,address).notice: Sets the updater address for a given organization (tenant).

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Checks if the contract supports a given interface.

transferPassportOwnership(address,addres.notice: Transfers the ownership of a battery passport.

updateOrgConfigUri(bytes32,string).notice: Updates the configuration pointer for an organization.

validateStatusTransition(uint8,uint8).notice: Validates the transition between battery statuses.

verifyIPFSHash(uint256,bytes32,bytes32,b.notice: Verifies the IPFS hash of a battery passport.
